div.div:
Drive firmware provides an MEK checksum to KMB when deriving an MEK. If the provided checksum is non-zero, it is compared with the calculated checksum. The operation fails (and the derived MEK is not sent to the encryption engine) if the provided checksum does not match the calculated checksum. This check is skipped if the provided checksum is all-zeroes.
Upon success, the calculated checksum is returned to drive firmware.
